think I was about six years

31:15.093 --> 31:31.729
old, six months old, when I thought of getting 
married. So, So I came back and I thought about

31:33.389 --> 31:39.163
getting married.

31:41.692 --> 31:48.520
Naturally, when you're a father, you feel bad. I 
was the first one. My father was very mortified and

31:50.722 --> 31:57.169
very hurt, but my father didn't say anything. But 
he did feel bad. The one who told my mother and the

32:02.235 --> 32:09.223
one who told my father was her. So I got married. El 
27. ¿En qué modo encontró con su esposo? Mi esposo

32:19.840 --> 32:27.139
era de...

32:19.840 --> 32:27.139
Él era de México. From Mexico? From which part? He 
was from Monterrey. Yes, his whole family was

32:31.956 --> 32:35.720
there in Monterrey. And he passed with papers to 
this side. And here he was. There he was working in

32:42.629 --> 32:43.950
that ranch too. There he taught himself to work. 
And well, in that ranch I met him. And one, I don't

32:50.018 --> 32:58.738
know, one no longer thinks, there are things that 
one doesn't think about when one is still old. And

32:58.758 --> 33:04.230
there are still things that one doesn't think 
about. In what year did your husband come to the

33:04.767 --> 33:10.533
United States? I think he came around... I think it 
was around... I'm not very sure, but I think it was

33:16.139 --> 33:23.927
around...

33:24.008 --> 33:27.531
I think he came around... around 23, 24. 23, 24. I'm 
not very sure. For what reason? For what reason did

33:31.556 --> 33:33.778
he come? Oh, well, he came for the same reasons that 
there is not much life there because the jobs are

33:34.012 --> 33:48.294
not like here. Not many have the opportunities. 
Now there are many opportunities. In those years

33:53.001 --> 33:56.627
there were not the opportunities that there are 
now. Now there are people who are very poor. Now

34:00.512 --> 34:02.737
there are people who don't have a school. Now there 
are people who don't have education. It's because

34:06.585 --> 34:11.014
they don't want it. Now they have all the 
opportunities. And Mexico too? Mexico, yes,

34:16.268 --> 34:30.472
there are also opportunities because I have been 
to Monterrey, I have been to Monterrey twice. And

34:30.492 --> 34:38.325
now that I have been alone with my children, I have 
been twice before. And I have seen that there are

34:38.710 --> 34:45.885
very poor people, but most of the people have their 
jobs, and very good jobs that many people in Mexico

34:46.287 --> 34:55.756
have. The poorest people have very good jobs to 
maintain themselves. Because they sell their

35:05.206 --> 35:12.733
things that they sell, very pretty, and any of 
those things need to be studied. And they have

35:13.557 --> 35:20.867
them, that's why they learn them, and that's why 
they make their lives. But I'm going to tell you

35:21.467 --> 35:30.119
that Mexico, as you know, I only know it because 
I've heard it and because they tell me about it. But

35:30.820 --> 35:34.144
yes, Mexico is very rich. As they say, Mexico is 
sitting in gold. But yes, What's the point of me

35:41.063 --> 35:49.354
being very rich and having the money saved here? 
You don't put it to work for the poor. You don't put

35:53.098 --> 35:55.702
it to help your own people. No. You want to have it. 
You use it a lot. You just think about being well. In

36:07.321 --> 36:09.023
having everything, only you. You have 
everything, you don't know about the others. And

36:14.789 --> 36:20.556
that's what I see, that it's not right. Because 
having your money, why don't you put it to work? So

36:27.744 --> 36:34.071
that that family doesn't suffer, the poorest one 
like you, doesn't suffer. put it to work and you

36:34.473 --> 36:39.040
will see how there is no poverty. Even if it is a 
little, like here when the United States started

36:40.422 --> 36:51.539
to pay little by little, but people knew how to 
support themselves. Well, there should have been

36:56.984 --> 37:03.931
Like those who have so much money, put them to work 
so that those poor people don't suffer. Many of

37:04.332 --> 37:12.320
those people have died, many, in these states. 
Why? Because there are many who have a lot of family

37:13.621 --> 37:20.849
and they don't have to keep them. And that's why 
they come to these places. because the money is

37:23.579 --> 37:28.087
saved there from those who have it, they don't give 
them what they lack. That's what I take badly

37:28.208 --> 37:31.915
there. And Yacina is, because I say on my part, I 
have gone a little, here to Laredo, here to Laredo,

37:31.935 --> 37:46.161
this to Monterrey, Yo tengo todo esto que no uso. Yo 
fui la otra vez. Yo llevé como cuatro o cinco

37:52.610 --> 37:56.094
paquetes. Yo los anduve repartiendo allí a esa 
gente que está de atiro pobre. Yo no lo necesito. Yo

38:03.582 --> 38:04.964
se los llevé a ellos. Porque a mí, yo no quiero tirar 
esto y tirar lo otro. Nosotros tenemos abastecido

38:11.571 --> 38:15.436
aquí, gracias a Dios. Bueno. We don't like it 
anymore. We don't like this food anymore.

38:24.425 --> 38:24.685
Everything. No, if God punishes us too. That's not 
good. If you go... Look, there are times when I have

38:28.690 --> 38:35.138
penises. I'm collecting penises, penises, 
penises. I have many penises, or nickels, or

38:37.561 --> 38:41.165
whatever. I carry many nickels in my wallet. I take 
them out with all the people I see who need nickels.

38:47.052 --> 38:47.873
I give it to them. I'm not going to be richer if I give 
a nickel and a dime. That's not going to help me. No.

38:58.474 --> 38:59.676
What I have is good. I don't envy anyone. I don't 
envy anything. Because I don't have those years. I

39:09.851 --> 39:11.093
don't envy anything. Nothing good. I go there, I 
tell you, I give away all the packages, packages,

39:13.678 --> 39:19.468
packages of clothes, of what I carry there. I give 
it to the poor people. I give the money to the poor

39:21.712 --> 39:24.677
people. That's why I carry what I carry loose to 
give away. I am here, where I can earn a nickel. Yo

39:34.799 --> 39:41.986
aquí estoy, yo hago mis costuras, yo hago mis 
delantares, yo hago horquilleros. ¿Yo puedo

39:42.006 --> 39:43.968
ganar un peso? Allá no. Esa gente no tiene, no tiene 
dinero para comprar un pedazo de material porque

39:46.231 --> 39:52.057
no lo tienen. Bueno, entonces, yo si lo tengo, 
ahorita no lo tengo, al ratito lo tengo y allá no.

39:58.804 --> 39:59.064
¿Ves? Porque ellos no tienen con qué ponerse a 
trabajar, monchos. And

40:02.828 --> 40:07.534
that's what makes a lot of money. It's like me, I'm 
doing very well here, I have everything here.

40:13.461 --> 40:16.564
Those people need a piece of bread, and I'm eating 
it. I don't need poverty, I'm not in poverty, I'm

40:17.165 --> 40:22.051
not in anything. I'm living very peacefully and 
everything. I don't know about the others. And

40:26.656 --> 40:27.958
that's what's not good. That's not good, and I'm 
not right about that. So, I got married on the 27th.

40:44.264 --> 40:47.628
I got married. Well, I got out of my house well 
because I didn't think about it. It was hard for me

40:56.129 --> 40:57.791
and all that. I thought, my mom and dad put in four 
months for me to get married. Well, I waited

41:04.361 --> 41:15.618
because I said, if they don't say yes, well, I'm 
going to stay. So,

41:15.738 --> 41:20.625
the year came, my little boy. He is now 40 years old. 
He is the oldest and he is in the service. Well, nine

41:25.897 --> 41:27.781
of my family came. There are nine of my children. 
Five men and three women.

41:39.986 --> 41:42.090
So I... The first time I went to the West, I went here 
nearby. The first time I went out, it was with my boy

41:48.295 --> 41:55.325
when he went to the service. Because my boy said, 
Mom, I'm going to go to the service. He said, he

42:00.772 --> 42:04.638
registered when he was 18 years old, which was when 
the war was. In this second war. The World War II.

42:10.165 --> 42:11.487
The World War II. Then he told me, Mom, we've never 
gone out of here. And I want us to go to Las Piscas

42:20.577 --> 42:30.889
this year, he said, because I'm going to leave next 
month. So I had my bad dad, and I had my mom and my

42:31.230 --> 42:37.137
grandparents who had died. Mi abuelito murieron 
el 37, murió mi abuelito. Y el 45 murió mi abuelita.

42:51.744 --> 42:55.069
Y el 45 mismo se fue mi muchacho al servicio. Pues 
que entonces yo,

42:57.513 --> 43:04.002
cuando yo, Cuando yo me casé, yo pensé nunca irme de 
fuera de ellos. Porque yo pensé todo el tiempo, si

43:12.258 --> 43:18.543
yo me casaba, estar todo el tiempo al lado de ellos. 
Pero entonces cuando yo, mi muchacho me dijo que me

43:19.864 --> 43:27.371
fuera, mi papá estaba malo. Y yo fui y le dije a mi 
papá que yo me iba a retirar de aquí. Y que me iba a ir.

43:36.010 --> 43:36.751
to the north. So my father says to me, well, I'm 
happy that you're leaving with your family,

43:37.712 --> 43:53.692
because I know that you're not having a good life. 
And maybe you can get a little better so that the

43:53.913 --> 44:00.261
boys can help you and you can leave. Well, I didn't 
feel very good leaving because my father was sick.

44:05.896 --> 44:16.546
But my Lord had promised me all the time that He 
would never take me out of my parents'

44:05.896 --> 44:16.546
side. But He never knew this. But that's how it was. 
He did fulfill what He told me. But because of Him, I

44:27.135 --> 44:32.600
lost my father because I never saw him again. 
Because on that trip, I lost him. But who caused it?

44:36.908 --> 44:38.771
Well, it was him. Because if he had seen the states 
with so many people at ease, I wouldn't have left

44:38.791 --> 44:45.904
this state. So we went. Thank God, we went back.

44:56.099 --> 45:00.225
I never received a telegram from my father. I never 
heard from him. Until I was on the ground, I knew

45:02.749 --> 45:06.155
that my father had died. It was impossible to come 
because they had buried him. So I went back. My son

45:17.332 --> 45:23.642
had the opportunity to go to Monterrey. to see his 
uncles, because his whole family is there. Yes.

45:30.354 --> 45:36.260
Then he said, Mom, give me money to go see my uncles. 
Yes. And he went with his cousin to Monterrey. A

45:41.766 --> 45:45.450
week passed and he came back. Then he went to the 
service. Then the second one stayed, the one who

45:49.514 --> 45:53.578
followed him. Que fue mi muchacho.

